    mdxType: "MDXLayout"
  }), mdx("p", null, "The book Escaping the Build Trap by Melissa Perri describes why product development efforts often fail and what needs to happen for organizations to become product-led. The book is one of the best overall descriptions of how a product-led organization should function and what the role of a product manager should be in such an organization."), mdx("h3", null, "Book Summary"), mdx("p", null, "Build trap is a term Perri uses to describe a situation where an organization is stuck measuring success by the number of features or products delivered, rather than by the business outcomes those features and products result in. "), mdx("p", null, "Escaping the build trap is important to stay competitive. An output focused company will end-up developing features that don't solve customer problems and as customers are not willing to pay for such features. Perri describes how a company can get out of the build trap and become a product-led organization that optimizes for customer value."), mdx("h4", null, "What does a company in a build trap look like?"), mdx("p", null, "Budgeting, strategy work and product roadmaps are set on a yearly cycle. The company sees product strategy as a plan that lists what steps to take and what features or products to build. The feature list is passed down in the organization to the product teams that have the features as their goals."), mdx("p", null, "Product managers are measured by how well they are able to deliver the outputs, and not by what kind of business outcomes those outputs bring. As the PMs goal is to ship a certain set of features by a certain deadline, they are not incentivized to question whether building those specific features make sense. With output focused success metrics, user research is seemingly unproductive as the discovery work just slows down the development work. "), mdx("p", null, "As user research is neglected, the teams end up developing features that no one needs or wants, and that don't deliver business outcomes."), mdx("p", null, "The top management sees no movement in the business metrics and conclude that the product teams are failing. They come up with new features to build in order to fix the situation, and the process repeats itself again."), mdx("h4", null, "What does a  product-led company look like?"), mdx("p", null, "Making the switch from an output focused feature factory to a product-led company requires changes in the way strategy is set, how product management is seen and how product development investments are seen."), mdx("h5", null, "Strategy"), mdx("p", null, "Strategy in a product-led company is deployed in four layers: "), mdx("ol", null, mdx("li", {
